[TestWorkloadHelpSnapshots/create_secret_tls - 1]
Create a TLS secret from the given public/private key pair.

 The public/private key pair must exist beforehand. The public key certificate must be .PEM encoded and match the given private key.

Usage:
  ksail workload create secret tls NAME --cert=path/to/cert/file --key=path/to/key/file [--dry-run=server|client|none]

Examples:
  # Create a new TLS secret named tls-secret with the given key pair
  kubectl create secret tls tls-secret --cert=path/to/tls.crt --key=path/to/tls.key

Flags:
